{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"050a053f-c116-4ec4-8179-c822800fd76f","content":"Here's the plan for your RAG-based Q&A feature:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐      ┌──────────────────┐      ┌────────────────┐\n│  Docs/*.md  │─────▶│  Ingestion       │─────▶│  Vector Store  │\n│  (source)   │      │  Pipeline        │      │  (in-memory)   │\n└─────────────┘      │  ┌────────────┐  │      └───────┬────────┘\n                     │  │ Load .md   │  │              │\n                     │  │ Chunk text │  │              │\n                     │  │ Embed      │  │              ▼\n┌─────────────┐      │  └────────────┘  │      ┌────────────────┐\n│  User Query │─────▶└──────────────────┘      │  Similarity    │\n│  POST /ask  │                                │  Search (top-k)│\n└─────────────┘                                └───────┬────────┘\n                                                       │\n                                                       ▼\n                                               ┌────────────────┐\n                                               │  LLM Prompt    │\n                                               │  (question +   │\n                                               │   context)     │\n                                               └───────┬────────┘\n                                                       │\n                                                       ▼\n                                               ┌────────────────┐\n                                               │  Answer JSON   │\n                                               └────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Key Components\n\n### 1. Ingestion Pipeline (`POST /ingest` or startup hook)\n- **Load**: Read all `Docs/*.md` files from disk.\n- **Chunk**: Split each file into overlapping text chunks (~500 tokens, ~100-token overlap). Use heading-aware splitting — prefer breaking at `#`/`##` boundaries so chunks stay semantically coherent.\n- **Embed**: Call an embeddings API (e.g., OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small`) to convert each chunk to a vector.\n- **Store**: Save `{ vector, text, source_file, heading }` into the vector store.\n\n### 2. Vector Store (in-memory)\n- For this doc set size, an in-memory `List<DocChunk>` with brute-force cosine similarity is sufficient — no external DB needed.\n- Each entry holds the embedding float array, original text, and metadata.\n- Easily swappable later for Qdrant, Pinecone, or pgvector behind an `IVectorStore` interface.\n\n### 3. Query Endpoint (`POST /ask`)\n- **Input**: `{ \"question\": \"How do I install the product?\" }`\n- **Embed** the question using the same model.\n- **Search**: Cosine-similarity top-k (k=3) against stored chunks.\n- **Prompt**: Build a system prompt: *\"Answer using ONLY the provided context. Cite the source file. If unsure, say so.\"* — append the top-k chunks as context.\n- **Generate**: Call LLM (e.g., `gpt-4o-mini`) with the prompt.\n- **Output**: `{ \"answer\": \"...\", \"sources\": [\"getting-started.md\"] }`\n\n### 4. Packages Needed\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` | Unified AI abstraction (chat + embeddings) |\n| `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI` | OpenAI provider implementation |\n\n### 5. Project Structure (new files)\n```\nProductQA/\n├── Models/\n│   ├── AskRequest.cs          # Question DTO\n│   ├── AskResponse.cs         # Answer + sources DTO\n│   └── DocChunk.cs            # Chunk + vector + metadata\n├── Services/\n│   ├── IVectorStore.cs        # Abstraction interface\n│   ├── InMemoryVectorStore.cs # Cosine-similarity store\n│   ├── DocumentIngestor.cs    # Load → chunk → embed → store\n│   └── QaService.cs           # Embed query → search → prompt → answer\n├── Controllers/\n│   └── QaController.cs        # POST /ingest, POST /ask\n├── Docs/                      # (existing)\n├── Program.cs                 # Register services, config\n└── appsettings.json           # API key, model names, chunk settings\n```\n\n### 6. Configuration (`appsettings.json`)\n```\nRag:ChunkSize        = 500   (tokens)\nRag:ChunkOverlap     = 100   (tokens)\nRag:TopK             = 3\nRag:EmbeddingModel   = \"text-embedding-3-small\"\nRag:ChatModel        = \"gpt-4o-mini\"\nOpenAI:ApiKey         = (from env / user-secrets)\n```\n\n### 7. Implementation Order\n1. Add NuGet packages and `appsettings.json` config\n2. Create `DocChunk` model and `IVectorStore` / `InMemoryVectorStore`\n3. Build `DocumentIngestor` (file loading + heading-aware chunking + embedding)\n4. Build `QaService` (query embedding + retrieval + LLM prompting)\n5. Wire up `QaController` with both endpoints\n6. Register everything in `Program.cs`\n7. Test end-to-end with the two existing docs\n\n---\n\n**Trade-off notes**: The in-memory store keeps things simple and dependency-free for a small doc set. If docs grow to thousands, swap in a real vector DB behind the same `IVectorStore` interface. The `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` abstraction also lets you swap OpenAI for Azure OpenAI or Ollama without touching business logic.\n\nWant me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"56c808da-3e49-4331-b056-14c5ab1ddccf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me create a comprehensive plan for the RAG-based Q&A feature.\n\nThe project is a minimal .NET 10 Web API with:\n- A barebones `Program.cs`\n- No NuGet dependencies beyond the SDK\n- A `Docs/` folder with 2 small markdown files\n\nI'll create a plan covering architecture and implementation steps.","outputTokens":1554,"requestId":"3C02:164D4D:1C52341:20283A8:69E82EE5"},"id":"ba6f3ea6-3f62-4ebc-a113-031955e3eba7","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:14:28.778Z","parentId":"2a56415b-11aa-4411-b954-747e37899443"}
